message: I voted tonight for the HEROES 2 Act after having conversations all across #ia01 with fire fighters like Ryan, who need the critical funding this bill will provide for our fire fighters and emergency medical professionals. https://t.co/R6ilHqrYxc

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: I voted for this package after hearing from so many Iowans who are struggling right now and need our urgent help. This is about helping our working families, our small businesses, firefighters, teachers, nurses and so many more #ia01 families.

name: Abby Finkenauer
message:
Iowans need relief & they need it now. We pushed for months for compromise & Dems moved closer while the Senate refused to come to the table.

Tonight I voted for HEROES 2 to provide long-overdue #COVID relief and crucial FEMA funding for #ia01 families impacted by these crises.

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: But it’s clear that the missing piece is the Senate. As the window for a deal begins to close, I urge my Senate colleagues to work with us to get this done. We owe Iowans more than political posturing #IA01.

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: I’ve been hearing from Iowans for months about the need for additional relief to get through the pandemic, and I’ve shared those stories with leadership in the House and Senate to push them back to the negotiating table for a bipartisan aid package. #IA01

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: I’m encouraged by the news of ongoing COVID-19 relief negotiations between House leadership and the White House, and I hope we’re close to a deal that delivers the help our families, small businesses, first responders and local governments desperately need. #IA01

name: Abby Finkenauer
message:
I’ve introduced more than 20 bipartisan bills in Congress, and 81 percent of my votes have been bipartisan. 

I didn’t come to Congress to get into petty political fights — I came to work for the people of #IA01.

name: Abby Finkenauer
message:
I come from a proud union family, and I’m working every day for Iowa’s working families. That’s why I’m honored to have the backing of *OVER 500* (!!) unions statewide. 

On #LaborDay, I want to recognize each one for their support & their fight for #IA01's workers:

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: On #LaborDay, we thank the Iowa workers who make our state a great place to live, and the unions that fight *every single day* to support them. This is a hard-earned holiday, made possible by generations of workers who secured the rights we enjoy today. #IA01

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Thrilled that we recently secured a $1 million grant for @NEI3A to create an SMP resource center to help Iowa's seniors and their families with Medicare medical billing errors and investigations into possible fraud or abuse. #IA01 https://t.co/8ppBUdW1es

name: Abby Finkenauer
message:
My grandfather has always been my hero. As a Dubuque firefighter, he taught me what public service truly means.

Whether I’m working to lower drug prices or fighting to help family farms survive, I always think of his example of service and duty. #ia01 https://t.co/DeTI7S7Onr

name: Abby Finkenauer
message:
Weeks after the #IowaDerecho, there is still critical work to do on the ground. I’m so grateful for all of those who have donated their time and resources to help Iowans in need. #ia01

https://t.co/Ck1PoZReyx

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Three new USDA Rural Development Project loans are being granted to improve sewer and wastewater systems in #IA01. I am happy to see these important projects receiving support from the USDA and look forward to seeing the improvement in Iowans’ daily lives. https://t.co/w5g22wRPUr

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Providing access to training opens up more opportunity in #IA01. I’m happy to see an investment in Dubuque & excited for new opportunities that will come from the training & assistance ECIA will provide. https://t.co/bU03fiFhCp

name: Abby Finkenauer
message:
The COVD-19 pandemic has created another serious challenge for our childcare providers. My bill to provide additional resources and safety information passed the House with big support from Democrats and Republicans. #IA01
https://t.co/3iwh8fo6Wd

name: Abby Finkenauer
message:
We need to improve our housing options in rural communities. Our bipartisan Protect Rural Housing Act would help bring better quality and more affordable housing to #IA01 towns.
https://t.co/Z7QoM3NCfS

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Lack of affordable and quality childcare has created a crisis for hard-working Iowa families. We worked across the aisle on the COACH Act to help more independent care providers start up their businesses to meet demand. #IA01 https://t.co/02BCyDhr9Y

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Too many rural #IA01 homes and businesses still lack access to high-speed internet. I brought the FCC to our communities to ensure they understand the need that exists — and do something about it. https://t.co/et4fKY06iD https://t.co/lZoKaVjQQz

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Representing Iowa's first Congressional District means working with anybody who’s serious about improving lives of working people. Over the last two years, I've worked across the aisle to introduce 25 bills with Republican cosponsors. #IA01 https://t.co/LK4ZZQrqEn

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Small businesses can’t always access markets abroad as easily as big corporations. That's why I put in the bipartisan work to extend and improve on the State Trade Expansion Program. https://t.co/f9NJgkW5t8 https://t.co/28XKQmHGwf

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Whether it's answering your policy questions or helping connect you with community resources, speaking directly with constituents is the greatest honor of being your congresswoman. #IA01 https://t.co/TKmM7T9W66

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Iowa communities devastated by the August derecho will receive a federal grant to help create cleanup jobs. This will provide immediate jobs for displaced workers and help clean up and rebuild #IA01 communities. https://t.co/mXMu01FvNT

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: From the beginning, we knew we had to control COVID-19’s spread, protect frontline workers, save small businesses and support folks whose jobs were impacted. The bipartisan CARES Act was a major step to get us through the early days of the pandemic. #IA01 https://t.co/h3milo2vJA https://t.co/gTrLOgGW2r

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: High-speed internet is essential to the health, education and economic opportunity of families, small businesses and farmers in Iowa. We’re happy the USDA is awarding a grant for broadband internet expansion in Mitchell County. #IA01 https://t.co/lhbPkNjmRd

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Extending the biodiesel tax credit is a great example of what can be done when we work across the aisle, and when the House & Senate work together on behalf of the people we serve. #IA01 https://t.co/BIRl0jIlA3 https://t.co/KDliZ9vjhB

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: As a member of the House Transportation and Infrastructure Committee I have worked hard to make sure leadership understands our community's needs, and ensured our priorities were part of major infrastructure investment legislation. #IA01 https://t.co/vgAHNBMB4w https://t.co/GpZGyGigIw

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: I also listened to our #IA01 small business owners, and used their insights to introduce and pass the bipartisan STEP Act, which cuts red tape and makes it easier to small businesses to access foreign markets. https://t.co/f9NJgldGRI https://t.co/vRUdjrqCgm

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: From virtual schoolwork to precision farming to telemedicine, high speed internet is critical in rural #IA01. I brought one of the FCC’s commissioners to our district to see first-hand how some communities lack basic access. https://t.co/et4fKY06iD https://t.co/azTvBGjZmP

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: I am happy to support the bipartisan CERTS Act. This will provide much-needed relief to our transportation sector and its hard-working employees. #IA01 https://t.co/TncMqrrEB8

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Our district needs new investments in roads and bridges. I’ve worked hard to ensure our communities’ priorities were included in a historic infrastructure package. #IA01 https://t.co/vgAHNBMB4w https://t.co/ae0jWfoRIY

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Navigating complex government agencies can be tough, which is why I'm so grateful for our amazing district representatives who help Iowans cut through red tape. If you need help with a government agency, don’t hesitate to contact our office. https://t.co/8sLpZHTNDx  #IA01 https://t.co/Gyfmt7SunH

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Iowa and other states are using a loophole to get around Buy America & fair wage requirements. We passed the Stop Swaps, Protect Local Jobs Act to close that loophole & ensure infrastructure projects are built with quality materials and local labor. #IA01 https://t.co/VcWBUbg3y1 https://t.co/pyd1t0PfPy

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: We’ve worked across the aisle on 25 bipartisan bills because I’m committed to working with anybody who’s serious about improving the lives of folks in #IA01 https://t.co/LJd9bUQw8x

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Drug commercials encourage you to ask your doctor to prescribe a drug, but they don’t tell you how the Rx will cost you. Well, I think you should know that price — so I passed a bipartisan amendment requiring Big Pharma to tell you. #IA01 https://t.co/uouP54W9Gb https://t.co/OS9zlQnesa

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: While we couldn’t meet in person for much of this year, we used our telephone townhalls to help connect #IA01 with invaluable resources and information to help them get through the COVID-19 pandemic and recover from August’s derecho. https://t.co/g7dbzzeHCB

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: I worked across the aisle and with our senators to secure a historic five-year extension of the Biodiesel tax credit, providing needed long-term stability for Iowa farmers and producers. #IA01 https://t.co/BIRl0jIlA3 https://t.co/llnWLYbDl3

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: States like Iowa should not be allowed to dodge fair-wage protections or Buy America requirements for our roads and bridges. We passed the Stop Swaps, Protect Local Jobs Act to close the loophole. #IA01 https://t.co/VcWBUbg3y1 https://t.co/1d2Q96EDlP

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: As we fight to lower the cost of prescription drugs, we also need to fight for more transparency from Big Pharma. That’s why I passed a bipartisan amendment requiring drug companies to disclose prices in their TV commercials. #IA01 https://t.co/uouP54W9Gb https://t.co/osvUDEnVcl

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Whether it’s recovering benefits held up by a paperwork issue or directing folks to the right agency, our casework team makes a real difference in #IA01. If you need help with a government agency, please contact our office. https://t.co/8sLpZHTNDx https://t.co/CGXUQJyuav

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Small businesses are struggling to survive the #COVID pandemic. I was proud to help pass the HEROES 2.0 relief package to ensure our local favorites will still be around when we come out on the other side of this crisis. #IA01 https://t.co/o0eklEKvly

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: The bipartisan CARES Act was a major first step in helping our communities and families make it through the COVID-19 pandemic. Now it is time for us to act again. The Senate and White House must join us in passing additional aid to help #IA01. https://t.co/h3milo2vJA https://t.co/bDqyTzbT0X

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Are you interested in serving your country in the U.S. military? Want to get a world-class education? Join us next Monday for a virtual service academy night to hear directly from academy representatives about the application and nomination process. #IA01 https://t.co/xijytB9uTn

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Our rural health care systems were challenged long before the arrival of COVID-19. Nov. 19 is National Rural Health Day, and I’m proud to introduce a bipartisan resolution recognizing the importance of rural health & thanking our amazing providers in #IA01 https://t.co/7QwAeSGupO

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: We passed HEROES 2.0 to extend a lifeline to local airports hit hard by the #COVID pandemic. Now we need the Senate and White House to negotiate in good faith and get a deal done to save this vital industry and local economic engine. #IA01 https://t.co/Lz1cRJJjmm

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Are you curious about attending the U.S. Naval Academy, Air Force Academy, Coast Guard Academy, Merchant Marine Academy or West Point? Join our virtual military service academy night on Monday, October 26th to learn more about how to apply. #IA01 https://t.co/xijytARTuN

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Whether it's unemployment aid, economic impact payments, or support for police, firefighters and healthcare providers, our communities need a new #COVID relief package. I voted to pass HEROES 2.0, and I stand ready to work with the Senate and White House on a compromise. #IA01 https://t.co/2hBSfxjKJD

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Interested in serving your country after high school? Join us on Oct. 26th for a virtual military service academy night to learn more about the application process for attending one of the five military service academies. Visit our website to sign-up #IA01 https://t.co/xijytB9uTn

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: We passed the HEROES 2.0 Act to help keep our small businesses afloat as we continue to battle the COVID-19 pandemic — now it’s time for the White House and Senate to show us their commitment to get a deal done. #IA01 https://t.co/oeBMHjGJHT

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Our communities & workers on the front lines need help now to weather the financial and public health crisis caused by #COVID. Every day we spend waiting on the Senate and White House to negotiate in good faith is another day of uncertainty for our essential civil servants. #IA01 https://t.co/TSthSlDvxl

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Dynamic small businesses are essential to the economic health of rural Iowa. The Pivo Brewery in Calmar will receive a $49,990 USDA Rural Development grant to expand hard cider production. #IA01 https://t.co/RaY4OMWVIg

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: We passed HEROES 2.0 weeks ago to help our communities through the COVID-19 pandemic, but we’re stilling wait on the Senate and White House negotiate in good faith. Every day of delay is a heavier hardship on hard-working Iowans and communities in need. #IA01 https://t.co/SB6Yp1wDq9

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Are you interested in attending the U.S. Naval Academy, Air Force Academy, Coast Guard Academy, Merchant Marine Academy or West Point? Join us on Monday, October 26th for our virtual military service academy night. #IA01 https://t.co/xijytB9uTn

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Small businesses like Rodina in Cedar Rapids are what make our communities thrive — but they’re struggling to survive this pandemic. I was proud to help pass the HEROES 2.0 relief package to ensure these local gems can weather this crisis. #IA01 https://t.co/hL4KVqCD8G

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: The airline industry is being hit hard by the COVID-19 pandemic, and so have our local airports. I voted to help pass the HEROES 2.0 pandemic relief package to keep these economic engines running and ready for recovery. #IA01 https://t.co/7GwHz0YsCs

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: I hear it every day from families, business owners, local leaders and more — we need another round of pandemic relief. It’s past time for the Senate and White House to come to the table and find a compromise. #IA01. https://t.co/9JoB3AFT6c

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: I take government accountability and oversight seriously — because that’s what Iowans expect. So when @USTreasury botched the rollout of debit cards for pandemic relief, I stood up and got answers. https://t.co/2fR3pMHw6H #IA01 https://t.co/2HCKbkFbK2

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: The pandemic changed everything this year, but keeping in touch with Iowans and taking their stories to Congress is always my top priority. #IA01 https://t.co/3y8g9hM2XC

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: I voted to help pass the HEROES 2.0 coronavirus relief package to provide much-needed help to the small businesses that make our communities vibrant, special places to live and work. #IA01 https://t.co/gxOkyeAOJC

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: When we ask Iowans to keep working through a deadly pandemic, we owe them workplace standards protections to keep them safe. That’s what I’m fighting for.  #IA01 https://t.co/naGhoIeVAz https://t.co/nv4Q6QVywf

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Our first responders, healthcare workers and other essential service providers are struggling in the economic downturn caused by COVID-19. They need assistance and they need it now — which is why I helped pass the HEROES 2.0 pandemic relief package. #IA01 https://t.co/t8ENvNDHdU

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: We passed the CARES Act last spring to save our small businesses and help our families through this pandemic, and in the months since we’ve kept fighting to ensure aid reaches those in need. https://t.co/h3milok6B8 #IA01 https://t.co/15xQ7ZWCKZ

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Communities like Cedar Rapids need help to get through the COVID-19 pandemic. That's why we passed HEROES 2.0 Act –– and why we need the Senate and White House to come to the table now to help Iowans in need. #IA01 https://t.co/0i6UuggaCt

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Iowa families, businesses first responders and hospitals need relief now. I voted to pass HEROES 2.0, and I’ve called on Democrats and Republicans to quit playing games and get to work for Iowans in need. #IA01 https://t.co/gzcd67WAqO https://t.co/amzTiZ58Y0

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: We need our police, firefighters and first responders now more than ever during the pandemic — and they need help to get through this financial and public health crisis. It’s time for the Senate and White House to come to the table and get a deal done for COVID-19 relief. #IA01 https://t.co/iVUHl5Dz2Z

name: Abby Finkenauer
message:
Since the pandemic began, I’ve been fighting for Iowa.
I’ve listened to your stories: https://t.co/cCPgfmEIsP
I’ve passed legislation: https://t.co/3iwh8fo6Wd
I’ve held the administration accountable: https://t.co/2fR3pMHw6H
#IA01 https://t.co/kwRSapgmCp

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Our small towns and rural places face a housing crisis that makes it harder for families to settle down and get ahead. I’m introducing a bipartisan & common-sense bill to improve housing options in rural America. #IA01 https://t.co/Z7QoM3w1ok

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: The message from Iowans is clear: They’re hurting, and it’s time for Democrats and Republicans to quit the political games and pass a pandemic relief package for the American people. #IA01 https://t.co/cCPgfmEIsP https://t.co/uGBrVdUQi9

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Listening to your stories is essential to doing my job and delivering for Iowa — especially during a pandemic. #IA01 https://t.co/HKiVVZMCmE

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Iowans are working their tails off to keep food on our tables during the pandemic — we owe them the safety, dignity and peace of mind that comes with enforceable safety standards during this historic crisis. #IA01 https://t.co/naGhoIeVAz https://t.co/4DjBriM4aj

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: When @stevenmnuchin1 came before @HouseSmallBiz, I had some questions about @USTreasury’s troubled execution in providing prepaid debit cards to Iowa families — and I demanded answers. #IA01 https://t.co/2fR3pMHw6H https://t.co/5DIlE7OIlD

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Iowa families, small businesses and frontline workers are still hurting in the pandemic. This month, I helped pass HEROES 2.0 to provide another round of relief — and bring the Senate and White House to the table. https://t.co/gzcd67WAqO #IA01 https://t.co/DeJYBqMrwH

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: When the pandemic hit last spring, we passed the CARES Act to provide relief to Iowa families, workers, small businesses and first responders — and then we got to work making sure that aid reached the folks who needed it. https://t.co/h3milo2vJA #IA01 https://t.co/28DCUfW5Ja

name: Abby Finkenauer
message:
I’ve listened to your stories: https://t.co/cCPgfmEIsP
I’ve passed legislation: https://t.co/3iwh8fo6Wd
I’ve held the administration accountable: https://t.co/2fR3pMHw6H
I’m fighting every day to get us through this pandemic, and to come back stronger than before. #IA01 https://t.co/2BHMaVf8Vx

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Today we recognize Indigenous Peoples’ Day to honor the culture and perseverance of Native Americans. The history of native peoples is too often ignored and obscured, but our country is stronger — and more just — when we acknowledge their contributions and their struggle. #IA01

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: DERECHO HELP FOR SMALL BUSINESSES: Low-interest federal disaster loans are now available through @SBAgov. Visit https://t.co/qKnQQmUmRa or call (800) 659-2955 for additional information. The deadline to apply is May 3, 2021. #IA01

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Federally-funded infrastructure projects should be built with high-quality American materials by high-skilled local workers. That’s exactly what my Stop Swaps, Protect Local Jobs Act requires. https://t.co/VcWBUbxEpz  #IA01 https://t.co/mp9d0pgK3k

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Iowa’s rural roads and bridges are in dire need to repair and replacement — for our communities’ safety and economic future. I’m fighting everyday as your congresswoman to bring those investments to Iowa. #IA01 https://t.co/dQkciApwBk

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Democrats and Republicans came to together to defend the biodiesel tax credit and pass a five-year extension to provide critical stability and certainty for our producers. I was proud to lead that effort on behalf of our Iowa farmers. https://t.co/BIRl0jZWrB #IA01 https://t.co/9j7XEkhxrX

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: NEW SMALL BUSINESS ASSISTANCE: @SBAgov just announced low-interest federal disaster loans for Iowa small businesses impacted by the August derecho. Visit https://t.co/qKnQQmUmRa or call (800) 659-2955 for more info. The deadline to apply is May 3, 2021. #IA01

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: #IA01 contains thousands of miles of rural roads that are critical for farmers and rural families, but often under-maintained and potentially dangerous. I fought to secure new rural road safety funding in our new infrastructure bill. #IA01 https://t.co/JcOqnV1L9V https://t.co/SLffgL1p1V

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: When we passed WRDA, I fought to include provisions that cut red tape and increase local-federal coordination on flood-mitigation projects. These changes incorporate the lessons of the 2008 flood to improve protection for all Iowa communities. #IA01 https://t.co/sQqC1Kcbjg https://t.co/ArqxfjgDec

name: Abby Finkenauer
message: Infrastructure is a great investment. My Stop Swaps, Protect Local Jobs Act makes sure we get the best return on that investment by protecting Buy-America requirements and fair wage provisions for local workers. #IA01 https://t.co/VcWBUbxEpz https://t.co/Lou3Z1djUL

name: Abby Finkenauer
